{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-216-advances-in-uikit-animations-and-transitions"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Direct onscreen manipulation is the cornerstone of the user experience on iOS. iOS 10 includes new support for making onscreen interactions even more immersive and interactive. Dive straight into the philosophy and techniques of building completely interactive, interruptible animations in your apps.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"UIViewPropertyAnimator","text":"`UIViewPropertyAnimator`","type":"heading"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Features","text":"Features","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Familiar"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Interruptible","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Scrubbable","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Reversible"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Broad availability of timing functions"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Running animations can be modified","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC16-216-UIViewPropertyAnimatorImage"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Introduction","text":"Introduction","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewPropertyAnimator"},{"type":"text","text":" conform to two protocols: "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewimplicitlyanimating","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewanimating","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Thanks to these conformances, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewPropertyAnimator"},{"text":" can be used for view controller transitions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When creating a new animator, you’re also creating a new object conforming to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uitimingcurveprovider"},{"type":"text","text":", which dictates the timing function that you want that animation to use."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewAnimating"},{"text":" protocol definition:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["protocol UIViewAnimating {","  var state: UIViewAnimatingState { get }","","  \/\/\/ whether the animation is running or not","  var isRunning: Bool { get }","","  \/\/\/ whether the animation is running in the forward or reverse direction","  var isReversed: Bool { get set }","  var fractionComplete: CGFloat { get set }","","  func startAnimation()","  func startAnimation(afterDelay : TimInterval)","","  func pauseAnimation()","","  func stopAnimation(_ withoutFinishing: Bool)","  func finishAnimation(at finalPosition: UIViewAnimatingPosition)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewImplicitlyAnimating"},{"type":"text","text":" adds the implicit characteristics to this animator:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["protocol UIViewImplicitlyAnimating {","  optional func addAnimations(_ animation: () -> Void, delayFactor: CGFloat)","  optional func addAnimations(_ animation: () -> Void)","","  optional func addCompletion(_ completion: (UIViewAnimatingPosition) -> Void)","","  \/\/\/ Allows you to proceed from a paused animation with a completely different ","  \/\/\/ finish duration, and possibly even a different timing function.","  optional func continueAnimation(","    withTimingParameters parameters: UITimingCurveProvider?, ","    durationFactor: CGFloat","  )","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewPropertyAnimator"},{"text":" definition:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["class UIViewPropertyAnimator {","  var timingParameters: UITimingCurveProvider? { get }","  var duration: TimeInterval { get }","  var delay: TimeInterval { get }","  var isUserInteractionEnabled: Bool { get set }","  var isManualHitTestingEnabled: Bool { get set }","  var isInterruptible: Bool { get set }","  ","  init(","    duration: TimeInterval, ","    timingParameters parameters: UITimingCurveProvider","  )","","  class func runningPropertyAnimator(","    withDuration duration: TimeInterval,","    delay: TimeInterval, options: UIViewAnimationOptions = [],","    animations: (() -> Void)?,","    completion: ((UIViewAnimatingPosition) -> Void)? = nil","  ) -> Self","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Basic-usage","text":"Basic usage","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ define your timing function","let timing = UICubicTimingParameters(animationCurve: .easeInOut)","","\/\/ create the animator","let animator = UIViewPropertyAnimator(duration: 2.0, timingParameters:timing)","","\/\/ add your animations","animator.addAnimations {","  self.squareView.center = CGPoint(x: 800.0, y: self.squareView.center,y)","  self.squareView.transform = CGAffineTransform(rotationAngle: CGFloat(M_PI_2))","}","","\/\/ add optional completion block to be called","animator.addCompletion {_ in","  self.squareView.backgroundColor = UIColor.orange()","}","","\/\/ trigger the animation","animator.startAnimation()"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Pausing-and-reversing","text":"Pausing and reversing","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The cool part of having this ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewPropertyAnimator"},{"text":" object is that now it’s easy to, for example, pause the animation, reverse it, and start again:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["animator.pauseAnimation()","animator.isReversed = true","\/\/\/ will go backwards","animator.startAnimation()"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that the completion block will be called with a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewanimatingposition","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" instance, telling us where we are at when the animation has completed (possible values: ","type":"text"},{"code":".start","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":".end","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":".current","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":")","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Stop-animating","text":"Stop animating","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"UIViewPropertyAnimator","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" also comes with ","type":"text"},{"code":"stopAnimation(_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", what happens is that we update the actual view model value to the animating value at that instant.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"withoutFinishing"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter tells whether we should consider the animation completed or not:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If we pass ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the animation is not completed and it is expected to call ","type":"text"},{"code":"finishAnimation(at:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in the future to complete the animation (at that point the animator completion block is also called). Note that calling ","type":"text"},{"code":"finishAnimation(at:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will not have any animation, it’s up to you to make the final animation and then call ","type":"text"},{"code":"finishAnimation(at:)","type":"codeVoice"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["animator.stopAnimation(false)","animator.finishAnimation(.current)","\/\/ completion(.current) called"],"type":"codeListing"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If we pass ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", the animation ends right there and the object completion block is not called","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["animator.stopAnimation(true)","\/\/ completion(_) not called"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":3,"anchor":"Reversing","text":"Reversing","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Three ways:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"pause animation, reverse, start animation (as we’ve seen in pausing chapter)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"reverse (change ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isReversed"},{"text":" value) while the animation is running","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"add a new animation to go back to the original position, for example:"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["animator.addAnimations {","  \/\/ go back to initial state, for example:","  view.center.x = 150.0","  view.transform = CGAffineTransform.identity","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This last way is preferred as the final animation is more fluid. Note that, with this last way, the completion handler will be called with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".end"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter, as the animation ends in the position that we just specified."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Custom-View-Controller-Transitions","text":"Custom View Controller Transitions","type":"heading"},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See Apple’s article "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/library\/archive\/featuredarticles\/ViewControllerPGforiPhoneOS\/CustomizingtheTransitionAnimations.html","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for more."}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"View controller transitions basically are a bunch of interlocking protocols:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrollerinteractivetransitioning","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" (you create this)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrolleranimatedtransitioning","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" (you create this)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrollercontexttransitioning"},{"text":" (iOS creates this for you)","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"UIkit gets the objects that conform to these protocols via a delegate: it might be a ","type":"text"},{"code":"UINavigationControllerDelegate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", or it might be a view controller ","type":"text"},{"code":"UIViewControllerTransitioningDelegate","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"text":"If any of these objects can return an animated transitioning object:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"UIKit will bypass the built-in transition","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"(for non-interactive transitions) UIKit will call ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrolleranimatedtransitioning\/1622061-animatetransition"},{"text":" and pass a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewControllerContextTransitioning"},{"text":" object for you to use","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"(for interactive transitions) UIKit will call ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrolleranimatedtransitioning\/1829434-interruptibleanimator","type":"reference"},{"text":" and pass a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewControllerContextTransitioning"},{"text":" object for you to use","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Written-By","text":"Written By","type":"heading"},{"columns":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"zntfdr","type":"image"}]}],"size":1},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"zntfdr","text":"zntfdr","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","type":"reference","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributed Notes","type":"text"}],"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"|","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/"}]}],"size":4}],"type":"row","numberOfColumns":5},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Missing anything? Corrections? ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"Related-Sessions","text":"Related Sessions","type":"heading"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-205-Whats-New-in-Cocoa-Touch","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-219-Whats-New-in-UICollectionView-in-iOS-10","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-228-A-Peek-at-3D-Touch","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC15-229-Whats-New-in-UIKit-Dynamics-and-Visual-Effects","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC14-236-Building-Interruptible-and-Responsive-Interactions","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC13-218-Custom-Transitions-Using-View-Controllers","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC13-221-Advanced-Techniques-with-UIKit-Dynamics"],"style":"list","type":"links"},{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Legal Notice"}],"type":"strong"}],"type":"small"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All content copyright © 2012 – 2025 Apple Inc. All rights reserved."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Swift, the Swift logo, Swift Playgrounds, Xcode, Instruments, Cocoa Touch, Touch ID, FaceID, iPhone, iPad, Safari, Apple Vision, Apple Watch, App Store, iPadOS, watchOS, visionOS, tvOS, Mac, and macOS are trademarks of Apple Inc., registered in the U.S. and other countries."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This website is not made by, affiliated with, nor endorsed by Apple."}],"type":"small"}]}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC16","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","title":"Advances in UIKit Animations and Transitions"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16"]]},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (46 min)","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc16\/216","type":"reference","isActive":true}},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-216-Advances-in-UIKit-Animations-and-Transitions","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uiviewanimating":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewanimating","type":"link","title":"UIViewAnimating","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewAnimating"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewanimating"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uitimingcurveprovider":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uitimingcurveprovider","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UITimingCurveProvider"}],"title":"UITimingCurveProvider","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uitimingcurveprovider"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uiviewimplicitlyanimating":{"title":"UIViewImplicitlyAnimating","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewimplicitlyanimating","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewimplicitlyanimating","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewImplicitlyAnimating"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/wwdc16/216":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc16\/216","type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc16\/216","checksum":null},"https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/featuredarticles/ViewControllerPGforiPhoneOS/CustomizingtheTransitionAnimations.html":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/library\/archive\/featuredarticles\/ViewControllerPGforiPhoneOS\/CustomizingtheTransitionAnimations.html","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"here"}],"title":"here","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/library\/archive\/featuredarticles\/ViewControllerPGforiPhoneOS\/CustomizingtheTransitionAnimations.html"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-228-A-Peek-at-3D-Touch":{"type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"A Peek at 3D Touch","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"3D Touch adds a completely new dimension to the iOS user interface and introduces an entirely new way to interact with your iPhone. Explore the existing API and get introduced to additions in iOS 10 that allow you to push the boundaries of 3D Touch. Learn about best practices for incorporating 3D Touch into your apps, how to add support for Quick Actions, Peek, and Pop."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-228-A-Peek-at-3D-Touch","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-228-a-peek-at-3d-touch","role":"sampleCode"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uiviewanimatingposition":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewanimatingposition","type":"link","title":"UIViewAnimatingPosition","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewAnimatingPosition"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewanimatingposition"},"WWDC16-216-UIViewPropertyAnimatorImage":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC16-216-UIViewPropertyAnimatorImage","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-216-UIViewPropertyAnimatorImage.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontrollerinteractivetransitioning":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrollerinteractivetransitioning","type":"link","title":"UIViewControllerInteractiveTransitioning","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewControllerInteractiveTransitioning"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrollerinteractivetransitioning"},"https://github.com/zntfdr":{"title":"GitHub","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GitHub"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC14-236-Building-Interruptible-and-Responsive-Interactions":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC14-236-Building-Interruptible-and-Responsive-Interactions","type":"topic","title":"Building Interruptible and Responsive Interactions","abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to fluidly transition interactive UI elements from gesture-driven control to animated transitions. Take advantage of new iOS 8 behavior to smoothly transition between several animations on the same view. Discover architectural approaches to interfaces which remain interactive while they animate.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc14-236-building-interruptible-and-responsive-interactions","role":"sampleCode"},"zntfdr":{"alt":"Profile image of zntfdr","type":"image","identifier":"zntfdr","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontrolleranimatedtransitioning/1829434-interruptibleanimator":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrolleranimatedtransitioning\/1829434-interruptibleanimator","type":"link","title":"interruptibleAnimator(using:)","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"interruptibleAnimator(using:)"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrolleranimatedtransitioning\/1829434-interruptibleanimator"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-219-Whats-New-in-UICollectionView-in-iOS-10":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-219-whats-new-in-uicollectionview-in-ios-10","title":"What’s New in UICollectionView in iOS 10","role":"sampleCode","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-219-Whats-New-in-UICollectionView-in-iOS-10","abstract":[{"text":"UICollectionView is a powerful class allowing your app to manage and customize the layout of views. iOS 10 brings enhancements for better performance, easier layout and brings features you’ve been looking for. Learn how to make your apps richer and faster by using new features in UICollectionView and its sibling, UITableView.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"article"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC13-218-Custom-Transitions-Using-View-Controllers":{"title":"Custom Transitions Using View Controllers","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"View controllers now allow you to create custom transitions, giving you expanded control over your user interface. Learn how to take advantage of custom transitions by using powerful new animation APIs, explore changes with full screen layouts, and see how to use navigation controllers with collection views to create a truly immersive experience."}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC13-218-Custom-Transitions-Using-View-Controllers","role":"sampleCode","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc13-218-custom-transitions-using-view-controllers","type":"topic"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontrolleranimatedtransitioning/1622061-animatetransition":{"title":"animateTransition(using:)","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrolleranimatedtransitioning\/1622061-animatetransition","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrolleranimatedtransitioning\/1622061-animatetransition","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"animateTransition(using:)"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC15-229-Whats-New-in-UIKit-Dynamics-and-Visual-Effects":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC15-229-Whats-New-in-UIKit-Dynamics-and-Visual-Effects","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc15-229-whats-new-in-uikit-dynamics-and-visual-effects","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Dynamic interfaces create fluid and rich interactions. Hear about new dynamic behaviors that have been added in UIKit and how to take advantage of them in your applications. Gain a practical understanding of how to integrate dynamics with AutoLayout. Learn about enhancements to UI Kit Visual Effects.","type":"text"}],"title":"What’s New in UIKit Dynamics and Visual Effects"},"zntfdr.jpeg":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC13-221-Advanced-Techniques-with-UIKit-Dynamics":{"title":"Advanced Techniques with UIKit Dynamics","type":"topic","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc13-221-advanced-techniques-with-uikit-dynamics","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Go beyond the basics to learn how to combine dynamic behaviors to create rich interactions. Discover how to apply dynamics to view controllers, collection views, and your own view subclasses to create engaging layouts and transitions. Learn best practices to keep your app responsive and performing well."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC13-221-Advanced-Techniques-with-UIKit-Dynamics"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16":{"title":"WWDC16","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 8, Swift 3.0, iOS 10, macOS 10.12 (Sierra), tvOS 10, watchOS 3."}],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16","role":"collectionGroup","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16","type":"topic"},"https://":{"url":"https:\/\/","type":"link","title":"Blog","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Blog"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontrollercontexttransitioning":{"title":"UIViewControllerContextTransitioning","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrollercontexttransitioning","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrollercontexttransitioning","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewControllerContextTransitioning"}]},"WWDC16.jpeg":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","type":"topic","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"title":"WWDC Notes"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/uikit/uiviewcontrolleranimatedtransitioning":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrolleranimatedtransitioning","type":"link","title":"UIViewControllerAnimatedTransitioning","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewControllerAnimatedTransitioning"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiviewcontrolleranimatedtransitioning"},"WWDC16-Icon.png":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-205-Whats-New-in-Cocoa-Touch":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-205-whats-new-in-cocoa-touch","abstract":[{"text":"The UIKit framework provides the crucial infrastructure needed to construct and manage iOS apps, and UIKit continues to advance the state of the art for app design with many new features. Dive straight into new features across the iOS frameworks that allow your apps to take advantage of many new system services, as well as to offer services to other apps. This is your first stop to discover the many sessions to see about harnessing the power of iOS 10.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","type":"topic","title":"What’s New in Cocoa Touch","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-205-Whats-New-in-Cocoa-Touch"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contributions are welcome!"}],"title":"Contributions are welcome!","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/zntfdr":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/zntfdr","kind":"article","type":"topic","title":"zntfdr (332 notes)","role":"sampleCode","images":[{"identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg","type":"card"},{"identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg","type":"icon"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"No Bio on GitHub"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr"}}}